        <center><h1 style="color: white; margin-top: 60px;">Tips and Advices</h1></center>
        <center>
            <div class="instructions" style="line-height: 1.6; font-size: 20px;">
                <h3 style="margin-bottom: 10px; ">Conserve Resources</h3>
                <h4 style="margin-bottom: 30px; ">Here are ten practical tips to help you reduce your water and
                    electricity consumption:</h4>
                <ul style="list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 20px;">
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Switch to LED Bulbs:</strong> LED bulbs consume significantly less
                        electricity than traditional incandescent bulbs and last longer, reducing both energy usage and replacement
                        costs.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Install a Programmable Thermostat:</strong> This allows you to set
                        temperature schedules, reducing heating and cooling when you're not home, which lowers electricity usage.
                    </li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Take Shorter Showers:</strong> Reducing shower time conserves water and
                        the energy used to heat that water.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Full Loads in Dishwashers and Washing Machines:</strong> Running these
                        appliances only with full loads maximizes efficiency and reduces both water and electricity usage.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Use Cold Water for Laundry:</strong> Washing clothes in cold water
                        reduces the electricity used to heat the water, without compromising cleaning quality.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Fix Leaks Promptly:</strong> Leaky faucets and pipes can waste a
                        significant amount of water over time, so fixing them promptly saves water.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Unplug Unused Electronics:</strong> Many electronics consume power even
                        when off. Unplugging them can reduce unnecessary electricity use.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Water Plants in the Early Morning or Late Evening:</strong> Watering at
                        these times reduces evaporation and makes your watering more efficient.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Insulate Your Home:</strong> Proper insulation reduces the need for
                        heating and cooling, thereby saving on electricity.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Regularly Maintain Appliances:</strong> Well-maintained appliances
                        operate more efficiently, using less electricity and water.</li>
                </ul>
